The paper deals with the compilation and security of cryptographic protocols, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security and cryptography. The paper specifically focuses on the translation of protocol narrations to sequences of operations, which involves decision problems in formal protocol analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper also deals with the reuse of known results from the literature, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
